1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 { This study will be a deep exploration from the white side of the Najdorf. I would caution lower rated (probably even me included), aka <2200 lichess, away from learning these lines because people won't necessarily play them against you. Much more important is learning the ideas for white than the specific moves. } 6. Bg5 { Black has 2 main tries here: e6 and Nbd7, which will be explored throughout this study } *


[Event "Winning attempts for white in the Bg5 Sicilian Najdorf: 6...Nbd7 Bc4"]
[Date "2021.05.14"]
