1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 Nbd7 7. Bc4 Qb6 8. Bb3 e6 9. Bxf6 Nxf6 10. Qd2 Bd7 11. O-O-O O-O-O 12. Rhe1 Kb8 (12... Be7?! 13. f4 $14 (13. Kb1!? $14)) 13. Kb1 h5 14. h3! { Stopping Bg4 as in the other line } (14. f4?! d5! 15. exd5 exd5 16. Nxd5 Nxd5 17. Bxd5 Bg4 18. Bf3 Bxf3 19. gxf3 $10) 14... h4 15. f4 d5 16. exd5 exd5 17. Re5 $14 { White can focus on the isolated pawn and take it at a time when it doesn't activate black's bishop pair. } *


