1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 h6 8. Bh4 Nbd7!? { Can still transition into the proper Browne variation if black continues with Be7, Qc7, etc. So to have a consistent repertoire we should still play Qf3. } 9. Qf3 (9. Qe2!? { Objectively the best move from 2024 theory though. Avoids the main issues with this whole variation. But now we're not following chapters 6-10... }) 9... e5! { Black feints going into the Browne. Instead, we get a mess instantly. This move only works because the knight on e5 hits our queen, and g5 is coming to trap our bishop. } (9... Be7!? 10. O-O-O Qc7 11. Be2! { Transposing to the Browne variation. }) (9... Qc7!? 10. O-O-O Be7 11. Be2! { Transposing to the Browne variation. }) 10. Nf5 exf4 (10... Qc7?! 11. O-O-O $16) 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. O-O-O! { An improvement on Qxf4. } (12. Qxf4?! g6! 13. Ne3 h5! $10 { Amazingly, black's bishop pair will come to life here even though black has been moving pawns nearly every move. White has nothing and is in fact risking getting killed by the two bishops. https://lichess.org/5jZXqtwH/white#26 } { [%cal Gf8h6] }) 12... Bxf5 (12... g5?? 13. e5! Bxf5 14. exf6 $16 { Black will actually be punished for their sins on the open e file. }) (12... g6?? 13. e5!! Bxf5 14. exf6 $16 { Black will actually be punished for their sins on the open e file. }) 13. exf5 Be7 14. h4! { Probably the most precise way to play this. All Bg5 tricks are stopped forever. Moreover, the Rxc3 idea can now be handled with Rh3! } (14. Qxf4!? Rc8 $10 { The threat of Rxc3 is annoying. }) 14... Rc8 { If the queen leaves the defense of c3, Black has Rxc3, with complete equality. } (14... O-O 15. Qxf4 Rc8 16. Rh3!? $10 { Transposes to the main line. } (16. Bc4!? $10 { Perunovic, Milos - Tadic, Branko, 1-0, SRB-ch, 2007, https://lichess.org/AbA9HPsz } { Perhaps another way to play as well. If the bishop lands on b3, Rxc3 is no longer damaging. })) 15. Rh3! O-O 16. Qxf4 $10 { White needs to be on the lookout for Rxc3, b5-b4, and Qc7 lining up on c2. A typical opposite sides castling position where black is not worse. } { [%cal Gg2g4] } *


