1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Nbd7 8. Qf3 Qc7 9. O-O-O b5 10. Bd3 Bb7 11. Rhe1 Be7!? { Transitioning to what appears to be the mainline, but black isn't faced with the typical g4-g5 pawn push as in the mainline. } 12. Qg3 { Getting off the long diagonal prepares both e5 and Nd5. } (12. Kb1?! { I'm unconvinced by this waiting move. After Qb6, black gets a better version of the previous chapter. } 12... Qb6 13. Nd5?? Qxd4 14. Bxf6 Bxf6! $19 { [%csl Gb2][%cal Gd4b2,Gf6b2] }) 12... b4 (12... O-O-O?! 13. Bxb5 axb5 14. Ndxb5 Qb6 15. e5 Nc5 16. exf6 gxf6 17. Bh4 Rhg8 18. Qh3 Bxg2 19. Qe3 Bc6 20. Nd4 Bb7 21. Nf5! Bf8 22. Bxf6! exf5 23. Bxd8 Qxd8 24. Qh3 $14) (12... h6!? 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 14. Bxb5) 13. Nd5! exd5 14. exd5 { If white can play Nf5 and attack the pinned e7 bishop, then black is completely busted. } 14... Kd8! (14... Kf8?? 15. Nf5 Bd8 { [%cal Gf5g7] } 16. Bh6 $18) (14... Bxd5?? 15. Nf5! $18 Be6 16. Nxg7+ $18) (14... Nxd5?? 15. Nf5! $18) 15. Nc6+ Bxc6 16. dxc6 Nc5 (16... Qxc6 17. Bxf6 Nxf6 18. Qxg7 Re8 19. Qxf7 Ra7 20. Rxe7 Raxe7 21. Qxf6 $10) 17. Bh4! { [%cal Gg3g7] } 17... Rg8 (17... Bf8?? 18. Bc4 Ra7 19. Bd5 Kc8?? 20. Bxf6 gxf6 21. Re8+ $18) 18. Bf5 (18. Bxh7!? { Another interesting try, but I believe this leads to a position that black should be happy to enter into: } 18... Rh8 19. Qxg7 Rxh7 20. Qxf6 Rxh4 (20... Bxf6?? 21. Bxf6+ Kc8 22. Re8+ Qd8 23. Rxd8+ Kc7 $18 24. Rxa8 $18) 21. Qxf7 Rh8 22. Re5! Na4 23. Re3 $15) 18... a5 (18... Qxc6 19. Bxh7 Re8 20. Rxe7 Rxe7 21. Qxg7 Nxh7 22. Qxf7 Ra7 23. Qxh7 Qe4 24. Qxe4 Nxe4 25. Rd4 Kc8 26. Bxe7 Rxe7 $10) 19. Qe3 { [%cal Ge3c5] } 19... Ne6 20. Bh3 Re8 21. f5 Nf8 22. g4 Qxc6 23. g5 Kc7 24. Qd4 N6d7 25. f6 (25. Qxg7? Ne5 $15 { White's queen gets trapped in Siberia. Black should probably have the advantage if they can quickly break through on the queenside. }) 25... gxf6 26. gxf6 Bxf6 27. Bxf6 Rxe1 28. Rxe1 Ne6 29. Bxe6 fxe6 30. Rxe6 Qh1+ 31. Qd1 Qxd1+ 32. Kxd1 Rg8 33. Be7 Rg1+ 34. Ke2 Rg2+ 35. Kd1 $10 { Black has a perpetual check if they want it. Sadly, no winning chances here. } *


