1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. f4 Qb6 8. Qd3 Qxb2 9. Rb1 Qa3 10. f5 Nc6?! { A minor step in the wrong direction. Black must now transpose to the other chapter to keep chances. } (10... Be7 11. fxe6 fxe6 12. Be2 Nc6? 13. Nxc6 bxc6 14. Bh5+ { Transposing to the below line: }) 11. fxe6 fxe6 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. Be2 Be7? { Combining these two moves is an outright mistake, although quite difficult to punish. } (13... Qa5 $14 { Transposing to the other chapter is now necessary. }) 14. Bh5+!! Nxh5 (14... g6 15. e5! dxe5 (15... gxh5?? 16. exf6 $18) 16. Bxf6 Bxf6 (16... e4?? 17. Bxe7! $18 { [%cal Ge7a3] }) 17. Bxg6+ hxg6 18. Qxg6+ Ke7 19. O-O! $18 { Black's lack of coordination and unsafe king will be their undoing. }) 15. Bxe7 Nf4 (15... Kxe7?? 16. Nd5+ $18 { [%cal Gd3a3,Gd5e7] }) 16. Qd4 { [%cal Ge7d6,Gd4g7] } 16... e5 (16... Kxe7?? 17. Qxg7+ $18 { [%cal Gg7h8,Gg7e7] }) 17. Qxe5!! { [%cal Ge7a3] } 17... Qc1+ (17... dxe5 18. Bxa3 $16 { A better version for white than the mainline: the rook is well-placed on the b file. }) 18. Rxc1 dxe5 19. Bd6 Nxg2+ 20. Kf2 Nf4 21. Rb1 $14 { Carlsson, Pontus - Eriksson, Johan, 1-0, SWE-ch, 2011, https://lichess.org/V9VPqx2Y } *


